x4freetext: The DNA/PITHON nuclear simulator at Physics
This device was a flash x-ray source using a single
transmission line pulsed by a Marx generator.
It was used for investigation of photoexcitation from
The 1.5 to 6 MeV range was studied with two
fixed end-point medical linacs at the Department of
Radiology of the University of Texas Southwestern
Irradiations with nominal 4 MeV bremsstrahlung were
obtained with a Varian Clinac 4/100 linac.
Bremsstrahlung having a nominal end point of 6 MeV was
obtained with a Varian Clinac 1800 linac.
Irradiations in the 6 to 11 MeV range were
provided with the DNA/Aurora nuclear simulator,
located at the Harry Diamond Laboratories.
